### Component 1: GitHub API Client (`github_api.py`)

#### [NEW] [github_api.py](file:///c:/Capstonee/github_api.py)

- `fetch_profile(username)` → Fetches user profile (name, bio, avatar, location, followers, etc.)
- `fetch_repos(username)` → Fetches public repos (sorted by stars), extracts name, description, stars, forks, language, URL
- `fetch_languages(username)` → Aggregates language usage across all repos (byte counts → percentages)
- `process_data(username)` → Combines all data into a single dictionary ready for template rendering
- Uses GitHub REST API v3 (no auth required for public data, but supports optional token for rate limits)

---

### Component 2: Flask Application (`app.py`)

#### [NEW] [app.py](file:///c:/Capstonee/app.py)

**Routes:**
| Route | Method | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `/` | GET | Landing page with username input |
| `/generate` | POST | Fetches GitHub data, generates portfolio, returns preview |
| `/preview/<session_id>` | GET | Shows generated portfolio in iframe |
| `/download/<session_id>` | GET | Downloads the generated site as a ZIP |

- Uses session-based temp directories for generated output
- Error handling for invalid usernames, API rate limits, network errors

---

### Component 3: Site Generator Engine (`generator.py`)

#### [NEW] [generator.py](file:///c:/Capstonee/generator.py)

- Takes processed GitHub data + selected theme
- Renders the Jinja2 portfolio template with the data
- Copies CSS/JS assets into the output folder
- Bundles everything into a self-contained static site
- Creates a ZIP file for download

